<item>
            <title>[HIVE-2660] Need better exception handling in RCFile tolerate corruptions mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-2660</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The exception handling in nextKeyValueTolerateCorruptions treats IOException as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if EOFException, corrupt, can be tolerated&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If CheckSumException, corrupt, can be tolerated&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;else not a corruption, re-throw&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;But the compression code can also throw IOException in case of corruption, which will get re-thrown in this case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct way of handling IOException is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if BlockMissingException, re-throw.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if not BlockMissingException -&amp;gt; corruption, can be tolerated&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
